      "repair_reason": "- No repair lane is needed because the review found no concrete patch defect; the remaining action is normal maintainer review of the draft PR and required checks.; Cleared: The diff stays within app menu controller/test code and does not change credentials, networking, dependency resolution, CI, release scripts, or other security-sensitive surfaces. (sha=3e9360a2756196800fee0fc7a91dc7bf2f9de266)",
      "review_summary": "The branch defers closed attached-menu rebuilds until refresh work settles, keeps stale nonempty open menus during active refreshes, cancels closed-menu rebuild tasks on open/close/shutdown, adds DEBUG lifecycle logging, and extends status-menu refresh tests.\n\nReproducibility: yes. from source and submitted runtime proof, though I did not run the macOS UI path in this read-only review. Current main rebuilds stale menus synchronously on open, while the PR shows a refresh-in-flight path that keeps stale content and prepares the closed menu after refresh settles.",
